<!-- PRIORITY ROADMAP -->
<div class="sec">
  <div class="sec-title">Priority Roadmap</div>
  <div class="action-cards">

    <div class="ac ac-c">
      <span class="pill p-c">Critical</span>
      <div>
        <div class="ac-title">Fix JavaScript Rendering — Google Sees a Blank Page†</div>
        <div class="ac-body">Every page on the site — homepage, About, stock listings — returns empty HTML to search engines. Until this is fixed, no other SEO work will have any effect whatsoever.</div>
        <div class="tech"><strong>Evidence:</strong> web_fetch returns only the &lt;title&gt; tag. Zero body text, no headings, no nav links. site:1drivemotors.co.uk returns 0 indexed pages in Google.<br><br><strong>Fix:</strong> Enable Server-Side Rendering (SSR) or Static Site Generation (SSG) in your framework (Next.js, Nuxt, SvelteKit etc.), or add a pre-rendering service like Prerender.io. Verify with Google Search Console URL Inspection after deploying.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ei-stack">
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Effort</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ef" data-w="66"></div></div></div>
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Impact</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ei" data-w="100"></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac ac-c">
      <span class="pill p-c">Critical</span>
      <div>
        <div class="ac-title">Claim Google Business Profile + Submit Sitemap</div>
        <div class="ac-body">No GBP found anywhere. Used car buyers search Google Maps first. Without a verified listing, 1Drive doesn't appear in the map pack — the most clicked local result format — even after the JS fix.</div>
        <div class="tech"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Brand searches and Google Maps queries return no listing for 1Drive Motors. No sitemap found at /sitemap.xml or /sitemap_index.xml.<br><br><strong>Fix:</strong> (1) Create and verify a Google Business Profile at business.google.com. (2) Generate sitemap.xml via your framework. (3) Submit to Google Search Console. These are independent of the JS fix — do them in parallel.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ei-stack">
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Effort</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ef" data-w="33"></div></div></div>
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Impact</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ei" data-w="100"></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac ac-h">
      <span class="pill p-h">High</span>
      <div>
        <div class="ac-title">Add AutoDealer Schema + Visible NAP to Every Page†</div>
        <div class="ac-body">No structured data found anywhere. Without AutoDealer JSON-LD and a visible address/phone in the HTML, Google can't connect this business to a location — locking it out of "used cars near me" results entirely.</div>
        <div class="tech"><strong>Fix:</strong> Add JSON-LD type AutoDealer to the homepage (and ideally every page via layout): name, address, telephone, openingHours, geo (lat/lng), url, sameAs (GBP URL). Add NAP visibly to the footer in plain HTML — not just in JS. Keep identical across site and GBP.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ei-stack">
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Effort</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ef" data-w="33"></div></div></div>
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Impact</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ei" data-w="66"></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac ac-h">
      <span class="pill p-h">High</span>
      <div>
        <div class="ac-title">Make the About Page Crawlable — GEO Score Is Blocked†</div>
        <div class="ac-body">The About page exists but its content is locked behind JavaScript. AI search engines (Perplexity, ChatGPT Search) can't read it — so they can't verify or recommend 1Drive Motors to anyone asking for a used car dealer.</div>
        <div class="tech"><strong>Evidence:</strong> About page URL confirmed by site owner. Content unverifiable — JS-rendered. No business description, staff names, or trading history found via any source including third-party searches.<br><br><strong>Fix:</strong> Part of the overall SSR fix. Once rendering is resolved, ensure the About page includes: trading name, who runs the business (first name + role), how long operating, location, what makes the stock selection different. 300+ words minimum for GEO credit.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ei-stack">
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Effort</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ef" data-w="33"></div></div></div>
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Impact</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ei" data-w="66"></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac ac-m">
      <span class="pill p-m">Medium</span>
      <div>
        <div class="ac-title">Add Meta Descriptions to All Pages†</div>
        <div class="ac-body">None detected. These are the two lines of copy in a Google result that make someone click your listing. Missing them means Google writes them automatically — usually poorly — cutting click-through rate even once you start ranking.</div>
        <div class="tech"><strong>Spec:</strong> 150–160 chars. Homepage example: "Browse premium used cars in London at 1Drive Motors. Quality-checked stock, transparent pricing. View current listings or call us today." Write unique descriptions for: homepage, stock listing page, individual car pages, About, Contact.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ei-stack">
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Effort</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ef" data-w="33"></div></div></div>
        <div class="ei-row"><div class="ei-lbl">Impact</div><div class="ei-track"><div class="ei-fill ei" data-w="66"></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

